Press - attack skill
------------------------------------------------------------
A Swashbuckler can spend most of their Flair to press a
controlled current opponent.

Your own active Challenge remains the strongest opening and grants a
full immediate attack round. Paralysis, freezing, or restraint of both
arms and legs grants one main-weapon attack sequence. Blindness, loss
of concentration, chilled, a movement lock, or lesser entanglement
grants one main-weapon swing and leaves a surviving foe Exposed for
four seconds. Silence and damage-over-time effects are not openings.

Press costs no spell points and has no timer. Every version costs the
same 8 Flair and requires the target to be your current opponent.

GL:  8
Cost: 8 Flair
command: press <target> (defaults to opponent if in combat)
duration: instant
see also: flair, challenge, status effects
